            <fr:title text="Noetherian space">Noetherian space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>3</fr:month>
              <fr:day>3</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link type="local" href="trebor.xml" addr="trebor" title="Trebor">Trebor</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A space is <fr:strong>noetherian</fr:strong> if every descending chain of closeds, or equivalently every ascending chain of opens stabilizes. In other words, the partial order of closeds is well-founded.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
